# Project structure

When adding or moving files in this repo, **use folders—avoid new loose files at the repo root**.

| Add… | Folder |
|------|--------|
| Slash command | `commands/<category>/` |
| Shared logic | `core/` |
| Views / tasks / handlers / API / DB | `views/`, `tasks/`, `handlers/`, `api/`, `database/` |
| Bot events & ClanBot | `bot/` |
| Secrets, `.gitignore` | `config/` |
| Database files | `data/` |
| Deploy (requirements, Procfile, mise, railpack) | `deploy/` |
| Documentation | `docs/` |

**Allowed at root only:** `run.py`, `README.md`, `railway.toml`, `railpack.json`, and hard links to `deploy/` or `config/` (`requirements.txt`, `runtime.txt`, `mise.toml`, `.gitignore`).

Edit canonical copies in `deploy/` or `config/`; do not duplicate content at root.

Full layout: `docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md`. Railway uses Railpack (`builder = "RAILPACK"` in `railway.toml`).
